{"model": "Qwen 3.5 27B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 130.3, "generation_tps": 21.1, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 55.6, "output": "Let $A$ represent Alice's current age and $B$ represent Bob's current age.\n\nFrom the first sentence, \"Alice is twice as old as Bob\", we can write the equation:\n$$A = 2B$$\n\nFrom the second sentence, \"In 10 years, Alice will be 1.5 times as old as Bob\", we can write the equation:\n$$A + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)$$\n\nNow, we substitute the expression for $A$ from the first equation into the second equation:\n$$2B + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)$$\n\nNext, distribute the 1.5 on the right side:\n$$2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15$$\n\nSubtract $1.5B$ from both sides to group the $B$ terms:\n$$2B - 1.5B + 10 = 15$$\n$$0.5B + 10 = 15$$\n\nSubtract 10 from both sides:\n$$0.5B = 5$$\n\nDivide by 0.5 to solve for $B$:\n$$B = \\frac{5}{0.5}$$\n$$B = 10$$\n\nSo, Bob is currently 10 years old.\n\nTo verify:\nIf Bob is 10, Alice is $2 \\times 10 = 20$.\nIn 10 years, Bob will be $10 + 10 = 20$ and Alice will be $20 + 10 = 30$.\n$30$ is indeed $1.5$ times $20$ ($1.5 \\times 20 = 30$).\n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9"}
