{"model": "Qwen 3.5 27B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_multiply__t2_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 105.6, "generation_tps": 21.3, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 61.9, "output": "To calculate $47 \\times 89$, I can break it down into simpler parts using the distributive property.\n\nStep 1: Break 89 into $90 - 1$.\n$$47 \\times 89 = 47 \\times (90 - 1)$$\n\nStep 2: Multiply 47 by 90.\n$$47 \\times 90 = 47 \\times 9 \\times 10$$\nFirst, calculate $47 \\times 9$:\n$$7 \\times 9 = 63$$ (write down 3, carry over 6)\n$$4 \\times 9 = 36$$\n$$36 + 6 = 42$$\nSo, $47 \\times 9 = 423$.\nThen multiply by 10:\n$$423 \\times 10 = 4230$$\n\nStep 3: Multiply 47 by 1.\n$$47 \\times 1 = 47$$\n\nStep 4: Subtract the result of Step 3 from the result of Step 2.\n$$4230 - 47$$\n$$4230 - 30 = 4200$$\n$$4200 - 17 = 4183$$\n\nAlternatively, using standard vertical multiplication:\n$$47 \\times 9 = 423$$\n$$47 \\times 80 = 3760$$\n$$423 + 3760 = 4183$$\n\nANSWER: 4183", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "f2fc3608f651"}
